PhenixCode RAG - Quick Start Guide
==================================

Quick Start:
# 0. Download and extract
unzip phenixcode-v1.0.0-linux-x64.zip

# 1. Configure settings.json to add proper embedding and completions endpoints

# 2. Or reset password explicitly
./phenixcode-core reset-password --pass MySecure123

# 3. Check password status
./phenixcode-core password-status

# 4. Embed full code (if running first time )
./phenixcode-core embed

# 5. Start server
./phenixcode-core serve --watch

# 6. After server is started, opening the UI will automatically connect to the server.
./phenixcode-ui
```

### **Access Web Setup:**
```
1. Open: http://localhost:8590/setup
2. Browser prompts: Username: admin, Password: <your_password>
3. Configure settings (no password field shown)
4. Submit â†’ settings.json created


Manual Start:
- Run "start.bat" to start in console mode

Service Management:
- Install: install-service.bat or install-service.sh
- Uninstall: uninstall-service.bat or uninstall-service.sh
- Status: nssm status PhenixCodeRAG (Windows)
- Status: systemctl status embedder-rag-core

Logs Location:
- configurable in settings.json

Troubleshooting:
- Check logs for errors
- Ensure port 8590 is not in use
- Run phenixcode-core executable directly to see console output

